#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:24
msgid "Dev Container"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:26
msgid ""
"The repository includes a standard devcontainer setup in `.devcontainer/`. "
"Using it is the quickest way to get a reproducible development environment "
"with CUDA Toolkit 13.0, LLVM 21, Clang 21, and the pinned Rust nightly "
"already installed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:31
msgid "The host does not need the CUDA Toolkit installed. It does need:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:33
msgid "an NVIDIA GPU"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:34
msgid "an NVIDIA driver compatible with CUDA 13.0"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:35
msgid "Docker with the NVIDIA Container Toolkit installed"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:37
msgid ""
"With a devcontainer-aware editor, open the repository and choose \"Reopen in "
"Container\" when prompted. The editor reads `.devcontainer/devcontainer."
"json`, builds the image, requests GPU access with `--gpus=all`, and opens "
"the checkout inside the container."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:42
msgid "For CLI-only usage, start the container with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:44
msgid "npx -y @devcontainers/cli up --workspace-folder .\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:48
msgid "Then run commands inside it with:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:50
msgid ""
"npx -y @devcontainers/cli exec --workspace-folder . cargo oxide doctor\n"
"npx -y @devcontainers/cli exec --workspace-folder . cargo oxide run vecadd\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:55
msgid ""
"If the host driver is too old, GPU commands such as `nvidia-smi`, `cargo "
"oxide doctor`, or `cargo oxide run vecadd` will fail inside the container. "
"Update the host NVIDIA driver rather than installing a different CUDA "
"Toolkit in the container."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:60
msgid ""
"If you use the devcontainer, you can skip the manual CUDA, LLVM, Clang, and "
"Rust setup sections below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:65
msgid "Nix / flake.nix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:67
msgid ""
"The repository also ships a `flake.nix` providing a reproducible dev shell "
"(CUDA 13, LLVM 22, Clang, pinned Rust nightly). Requires [Nix](https://nixos."
"org/download/) with flakes enabled, an NVIDIA driver on the host, and Linux "
"(x86\\_64 or aarch64)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:72
msgid "Inside the cuda-oxide repo — `cargo-oxide` is included in the shell:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:74
msgid ""
"nix develop\n"
"cargo oxide run vecadd\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:79
msgid "To bootstrap a new project without cloning:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:81
msgid ""
"nix run github:NVlabs/cuda-oxide#new my-project\n"
"cd my-project && nix develop\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:86
msgid ""
"This scaffolds via `cargo oxide new` and drops in a `flake.nix` that "
"inherits this repo's dev shell. The shellHook auto-discovers host NVIDIA "
"driver libraries on NixOS and non-NixOS systems; if the host driver is too "
"old, update it rather than changing what's inside the Nix shell."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:91
msgid ""
"If you use the Nix flake, you can skip the manual CUDA, LLVM, Clang, and "
"Rust setup sections below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:96
msgid "CUDA Toolkit"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:98
msgid ""
"Install the CUDA Toolkit from the [NVIDIA CUDA Downloads](https://developer."
"nvidia.com/cuda-downloads) page, then make sure it is on your `PATH`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:100
msgid "export PATH=\"/usr/local/cuda/bin:$PATH\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:104
msgid "Verify the install:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:106
msgid "nvcc --version\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:111
msgid ""
"If you installed CUDA to a non-default location, set `CUDA_TOOLKIT_PATH` to "
"its root directory (the one containing `include/cuda.h`). If unset, cuda-"
"oxide defaults to `/usr/local/cuda`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:116
msgid "Toolkit and driver compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:118
msgid ""
"The CUDA toolkit and NVIDIA driver are separate installations. A newer "
"toolkit can often run with an older driver through CUDA minor-version "
"compatibility, but that compatibility does not cover newer PTX:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:122
msgid ""
"cubin ───────────────────────────► driver loads finished GPU code\n"
"PTX   ──► driver compiles it ─────► finished GPU code\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:127
msgid ""
"The normal cuda-oxide path gets PTX from LLVM `llc`, so installing a newer "
"CUDA toolkit does not by itself change that PTX version. The NVVM forward-"
"execution path gets PTX from the selected toolkit's nvJitLink. If that PTX "
"is newer than the driver understands, module loading returns "
"`CUDA_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_PTX_VERSION` (error 222)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:133
msgid "For example, the toolchains used during current validation produced:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:135
msgid ""
"LLVM llc ───────────────► PTX 8.7 ──► driver 580 ✓\n"
"CUDA 13.3 nvJitLink ───► PTX 9.3 ──► driver 580 ✗ error 222\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:140
msgid ""
"These are observed versions, not permanent properties of the two paths. "
"Check the generated PTX `.version` directive when diagnosing another "
"toolchain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:143
msgid ""
"CUDA 13.x minor-version compatibility starts at driver 580, while CUDA "
"13.3's corresponding full-support driver is 610.43.02. A 580 driver can "
"therefore load compatible finished cubins, but it cannot JIT PTX 9.3 "
"produced by CUDA 13.3. See the [CUDA release notes](https://docs.nvidia.com/"
"cuda/cuda-toolkit-release-notes/index.html) for the current driver table."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:149
msgid "Upgrade the driver or select a compatible toolkit for the command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:151
msgid ""
"CUDA_TOOLKIT_PATH=/usr/local/cuda-13.0 cargo oxide run <example> --arch "
"sm_86\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:155
msgid ""
"See NVIDIA's [minor-version compatibility guide](https://docs.nvidia.com/"
"deploy/cuda-compatibility/minor-version-compatibility.html) for the "
"supported driver ranges and PTX limitation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:161
msgid "LLVM 21+ (optional)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:163
msgid "cuda-oxide uses LLVM's NVPTX backend to lower LLVM IR to PTX."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:165
msgid "Usually `llc` in Rust toolchain is enough."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:167
msgid ""
"Install LLVM 21 or newer and make sure `llc-21` (or `llc-22`) is on your "
"`PATH`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:169
msgid ""
"# Ubuntu / Debian\n"
"sudo apt install llvm-21\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:174
msgid ""
"If your distro packages do not provide `llvm-21`, use LLVM's apt helper:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:176
msgid ""
"sudo apt-get install -y lsb-release wget software-properties-common gnupg\n"
"wget https://apt.llvm.org/llvm.sh && chmod +x llvm.sh\n"
"sudo ./llvm.sh 21\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:182
msgid "Verify that the NVPTX target is present:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:184
msgid "llc-21 --version | grep nvptx\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:188
msgid ""
"You should see a line containing `nvptx64` in the registered targets. The "
"pipeline auto-discovers `llc-22` and `llc-21` in that order; pin a specific "
"binary with `CUDA_OXIDE_LLC=/usr/bin/llc-21` if needed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:193
msgid ""
"A stock LLVM build without the NVPTX backend will not work. The `llvm-21` "
"Ubuntu package includes it by default, but if you build LLVM from source you "
"must pass `-DLLVM_TARGETS_TO_BUILD=\"X86;NVPTX\"` to CMake."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:197
msgid ""
"**Why LLVM 21?** We emit TMA / tcgen05 / WGMMA intrinsics that `llc` from "
"LLVM 20 and earlier can't handle. Simple kernels might still work with an "
"older `llc` (set `CUDA_OXIDE_LLC=/path/to/llc-20`), but anything Hopper / "
"Blackwell needs 21+."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:202
msgid "Clang (host `cuda-bindings`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:204
msgid ""
"The host `cuda-bindings` crate runs [`bindgen`](https://github.com/rust-lang/"
"rust-bindgen), which loads `libclang.so` at runtime and needs clang's own "
"resource-dir `stddef.h` — a bare `libclang1-*` runtime is not enough. Three "
"packages cover both halves:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:206
msgid ""
"sudo apt install libclang-21-dev libclang-cpp21-dev libclang-common-21-dev\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:210
msgid ""
"`cargo oxide doctor` catches this up front; the symptom otherwise is "
"`'stddef.h' file not found` during the host build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:213
msgid ""
"**If doctor still reports clang not found:** The issue may be that the "
"versioned binary (e.g., clang-21) is installed but not mapped to the "
"unversioned clang command required by bindgen. You can fix this by "
"installing the clang meta-package, which manages these dependencies "
"automatically:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:216
msgid "sudo apt install clang libclang-dev\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:223
msgid ""
"**Fresh Ubuntu 24.04 / DGX-OS:** after installing LLVM 21 via `apt.llvm.org/"
"llvm.sh` as shown above, the versioned `clang-21` / `clang++-21` binaries "
"are present but the unversioned aliases `cargo oxide doctor` looks for are "
"not. Add them with `update-alternatives`:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:225
msgid ""
"sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/clang   clang   /usr/bin/"
"clang-21   100\n"
"sudo update-alternatives --install /usr/bin/clang++ clang++ /usr/bin/clang+"
"+-21 100\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:230
msgid "Validated on Asus GX10 / NVIDIA DGX Spark."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:235
msgid "Rust toolchain"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:237
msgid ""
"The workspace ships a `rust-toolchain.toml` that pins the exact nightly "
"version and required components. When you first run any `cargo` command "
"inside the repo, `rustup` will install the correct toolchain automatically."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:239
msgid "If you need to install it manually:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:241
msgid ""
"rustup toolchain install nightly-2026-04-03\n"
"rustup component add rust-src rustc-dev rust-analyzer --toolchain "
"nightly-2026-04-03\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:246
msgid "The two extra components are required by the codegen backend:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:248
msgid ""
"`rust-src` -- source of the Rust standard library, needed for cross-"
"compiling to the NVPTX target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:249
msgid "`rustc-dev` -- compiler internals that the backend links against."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:253
msgid "cargo-oxide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:255
msgid ""
"`cargo-oxide` is the cargo subcommand that drives the entire build pipeline "
"(`cargo oxide run`, `build`, `debug`, `pipeline`, etc.)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:257
msgid ""
"**Inside the cuda-oxide repo**, it works out of the box via a workspace "
"alias -- no extra install step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:259
msgid ""
"**For use outside the repo** (your own projects), install it with the pinned "
"nightly toolchain:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:261
msgid ""
"cargo +nightly-2026-04-03 install --git https://github.com/NVlabs/cuda-oxide."
"git cargo-oxide\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:265
msgid ""
"On first run, `cargo-oxide` will automatically fetch and build the codegen "
"backend. Subsequent runs reuse the cached build."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:269
msgid "Verifying your installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:271
msgid "Run the built-in diagnostics check:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:273
msgid "cargo oxide doctor\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:277
msgid ""
"`cargo oxide doctor` validates your Rust toolchain, CUDA headers (`cuda.h`), "
"CUDA toolkit (including libNVVM / nvJitLink / libdevice for kernels that use "
"math intrinsics), LLVM installation, NVIDIA driver / GPU, and codegen "
"backend in one shot."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:282
msgid ""
"`cargo-oxide` itself does not need the CUDA toolkit or an NVIDIA driver to "
"build and run, so `doctor` works even on a machine where nothing is "
"installed yet and diagnoses exactly what is missing (for example missing "
"`cuda.h`, or no driver). The driver / GPU check is informational: only "
"`cargo oxide run` needs a GPU, while `build` and `pipeline` work without one."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:288
msgid "Then build and run an example end-to-end:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:290
msgid "cargo oxide run vecadd\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:294
msgid ""
"If everything is configured correctly, this compiles a Rust kernel to PTX, "
"launches it on the GPU, and prints a success message."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:297
msgid "**Common issues:**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:299
msgid ""
"`No working llc-21 or llc-22 found on PATH` -- install LLVM 21+ (`sudo apt "
"install llvm-21`), add `/usr/lib/llvm-21/bin` to your `PATH`, or set "
"`CUDA_OXIDE_LLC=/usr/bin/llc-21`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:300
msgid ""
"`'stddef.h' file not found` when building host `cuda-bindings` -- install "
"clang dev headers: `sudo apt install clang-21` (or `libclang-common-21-dev`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:301
msgid ""
"`cuda.h not found` -- Set `CUDA_TOOLKIT_PATH` to your CUDA install root, or "
"ensure `/usr/local/cuda/include/cuda.h` exists."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../getting-started/installation.md:302
msgid ""
"`rust-src component missing` -- Run `rustup component add rust-src --"
"toolchain nightly-2026-04-03`."
msgstr ""
